      "title": "A Humane Meditation Instruction",
      "body": [
        {
          "text": "Sit in a way that lets the body feel supported rather than corrected. Let the breath be known where it is easiest to feel: nostrils, chest, belly, or the whole body breathing."
        },
        {
          "text": "When attention wanders, the return is not a failure. It is the moment the practice becomes visible.",
          "emphasis": true
        },
        {
          "text": "Heart slides should leave enough spaciousness for silence, while still giving the facilitator precise language."
        }
      ],
      "reveal": "sequence",
      "transition": "crossfade-soft"
    },
